'From Squeak2.9alpha of 12 June 2000 [latest update: #2594] on 10 September 2000 at 4:08:59 pm'!"Change Set:		WnldHack-arDate:			10 September 2000Author:			Andreas RaabA hack for faster #containsPoint: in Wonderlands w/o backgrounds. Since on each morphic cycle there are between 3-6 sends of #containsPoint: and since a mouse event is generated on each morphic cycle (even if nothing whatsoever happens) this hack gives much better responsiveness."!WonderlandMorph subclass: #WonderlandCameraMorph	instanceVariableNames: 'myCamera myControls eventFocus lastCursorPoint mouseUpButton firstPersonControls mode outline currentActor currentPosition currentCanvas currentColor currentNib lastPosition paintMode palette restore backup pickedPoint pickedActor '	classVariableNames: ''	poolDictionaries: 'WonderlandConstants '	category: 'Balloon3D-Wonderland Morphs'!!WonderlandCameraMorph methodsFor: 'drawing' stamp: 'ar 9/10/2000 16:04'!drawOn: aCanvas 	aCanvas asBalloonCanvas render: self.	self outline ifNotNil: [self sketchOn: aCanvas].	"*** hack ***"	pickedPoint _ nil.! !!WonderlandCameraMorph methodsFor: 'geometry' stamp: 'ar 9/10/2000 16:06'!containsPoint: aPoint	"Perform a full picking op if the camera does not draw the background"	myCamera drawSceneBackground		ifTrue:[^super containsPoint: aPoint].	"*** hack ***"	pickedPoint = aPoint 		ifFalse:[pickedActor _ myCamera pickAt: aPoint].	pickedPoint _ aPoint.	^pickedActor notNil! !!WonderlandCameraMorph methodsFor: 'stepping' stamp: 'ar 9/10/2000 16:04'!step	self changed.	"*** hack ***"	pickedPoint _ nil.! !!WonderlandCameraMorph methodsFor: 'object fileIn' stamp: 'ar 9/10/2000 16:08'!convertbosfcemmmelmfmoccccclpprb0: varDict bosfcemmmelmfmoccccclpprbpp0: smartRefStrm	"These variables are automatically stored into the new instance #('bounds' 'owner' 'submorphs' 'fullBounds' 'color' 'extension' 'myWonderland' 'myCamera' 'myControls' 'eventFocus' 'lastCursorPoint' 'mouseUpButton' 'firstPersonControls' 'mode' 'outline' 'currentActor' 'currentPosition' 'currentCanvas' 'currentColor' 'currentNib' 'lastPosition' 'paintMode' 'palette' 'restore' 'backup').	This method is for additional changes. Use statements like (foo _ varDict at: 'foo')."	"New variables: #('pickedPoint' 'pickedActor')  If a non-nil value is needed, please assign it."! !